ce:section.ce:para:
N doping endows CDs with more excellent inhibiting effects owing to its strong adsorption properties (Cen et al., 2019; Guo et al., 2022; Long et al., 2022a; Zhu et al., 2022). Hence, the employment of N-containing precursors conduces to improving the inhibition efficiency of CDs. The obvious regularity above is easily observed from previous studies, but it is quite difficult to explicate clearly the association between synthesis conditions of CDs and their corresponding inhibition properties. In this case, it is necessary to use ML to acquire hidden information behind the synthesis parameters, assisting researchers quickly choose the suitable reaction conditions. First of all, the dataset is created by combining 102 data points on CDs synthesis and inhibition efficiency from multitudes of reported studies and our own experiments. In detail, according to previous experience and existing research, CDs concentration in HCl, precursor type and quantity, solvent type and volume, reaction time and temperature possibly governing the inhibition performance of CDs are chosen as typical parameters. Since the precursor type and solvent type fail to directly input into the ML model, the precursor type is converted into two primary characteristics including N and C atomic content, while the solvent type is replaced by code figures (Number 1, 2, 3 and 4 represent ethanol, NaOH solution, distilled water and DI water, respectively). Naturally, these eight descriptors containing CDs concentration in HCl, N atomic content, C atomic content, precursor quantity, solvent type and volume, reaction time and temperature are regarded as features (Table 1
                        ). The inhibition efficiencies of CDs calculated by PDP act as the objective. It should be pointed out that the inhibition efficiencies of CDs are acquired only from the references utilizing CDs as corrosion inhibitors for Q235 carbon steel in 1 M HCl or 0.5 M H2SO4 at room temperature. In addition to extracting data of CDs from the published literature, 10 sets of data containing CDs synthetic conditions and inhibition efficiencies are collected by our experiments to perfect the dataset for ML. This contributes to ensuring the reliability of ML models in guiding the synthesis of CDs-based corrosion inhibitors. The inhibiting efficiencies of the as-prepared CDs at different concentrations are calculated by their PDP curves. The corresponding synthetic parameters of CDs and their inhibition efficiencies calculated by PDP are shown in Table S1. Subsequently, the pairwise correlation between different features is examined before ML model training. As presented in Fig. 1
                        a, all the pairs of features illustrate low linear correlations, testifying the validity of feature selection.
